(269, '_transient_doc_011a53ea111e3880f95057893715ada8', '<div id="ait-theme-doc">\n\n				<header class="page-header"><h1 class="page-title">\n						Frequently Asked Questions\n					</h1>\n				</header><section class="skin-list"><article id="post-480" class="post-480 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">1.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=hosting-requirements-2" title="Permalink to Hosting Requirements" rel="bookmark">Hosting Requirements</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Make sure your hosting supports the following modules</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-480 --><article id="post-821" class="post-821 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">2.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=i-can%c2%b4t-see-iconstext-in-visual-editor" title="Permalink to I can''t see icons/text in visual editor." rel="bookmark">I can''t see icons/text in visual editor.</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>If you have problems with your visual editor and you can’t use it, you can turn off our icons using file “config.php” in the root directory of the theme. If you don’t have config.php file, please create it. Just set value wysiwyg = disabled Please also refer to the following document.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-821 --><article id="post-850" class="post-850 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">3.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=impression-slider-not-showing-correctly" title="Permalink to Impression slider not showing correctly" rel="bookmark">Impression slider not showing correctly</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>If you have any problems with the view of the tab headings in the impression slider, please check if you havent install the WSD security plugin or any other plugin which changes the wordpress table prefix. Scripts commonly used in the themes work with the standard prefix of the wordpress tables. Standard prefix: wp_tableName Edited [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-850 --><article id="post-914" class="post-914 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">4.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=do-your-themes-support-wordpress-multisite" title="Permalink to Do your themes support Wordpress Multisite (WPMU)?" rel="bookmark">Do your themes support Wordpress Multisite (WPMU)?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Yes, themes support Wordpress Multisite no problem.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-914 --><article id="post-1426" class="post-1426 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">5.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-make-changes-in-css" title="Permalink to How to make changes in CSS?" rel="bookmark">How to make changes in CSS?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>A lot of our customers asked us, how to make some changes of styles on their sites. Based on your requests and questions, here is little tutorial how you can use developer tools in your browser. 1. Developer tools in your browser Developer tools allow you to edit, debug, and monitor CSS, HTML, and JavaScript [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-1426 --><article id="post-2233" class="post-2233 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">6.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-rate-theme" title="Permalink to How can I rate theme ?" rel="bookmark">How can I rate theme ?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>When you have purchased one of our themes, we will be happy to have rating from you on Themeforest site where you bought your theme. Just sign in with your credentials and you will be able to give rating for template, you can see on next image</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-2233 --><article id="post-2972" class="post-2972 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">7.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=my-google-analytics-code-doesnt-work" title="Permalink to My Google Analytics code doesn''t work." rel="bookmark">My Google Analytics code doesn''t work.</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>All our themes build on our AIT Framework provide option to insert Google Analytics tracing code in General Settings.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-2972 --><article id="post-365" class="post-365 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">8.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-disable-comments-on-posts" title="Permalink to How to disable comments on posts/pages." rel="bookmark">How to disable comments on posts/pages.</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>You can turn off comments on all existing articles, or disable comments globally for all articles.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-365 --><article id="post-369" class="post-369 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">9.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-set-up-home-page-and-blog-page" title="Permalink to How to set up home-page and blog-page" rel="bookmark">How to set up home-page and blog-page</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>In WordPress Admin go to Settings â &gt; Reading. Select âA static page (select below)â from âFront page displaysâ and choose one page from the dropdown for home-page (front-page) and one page for blog page: If the theme has special homepage template (layout) then go to your homepage and set homepage template:</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-369 --><article id="post-373" class="post-373 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">10.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-add-twitter-box-stream" title="Permalink to How to add twitter box (stream) shortcode" rel="bookmark">How to add twitter box (stream) shortcode</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>To show twitter box (stream) on post or page you have to insert twitter box shortcode to the page content. You can do it by clicking on the following button in WYSIWYG editor: Select twitter and insert your twitter username: You can insert twitter box into sidebar or into widget area as well:</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-373 --><article id="post-508" class="post-508 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">11.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-insert-google-map" title="Permalink to  How to insert google map" rel="bookmark"> How to insert google map</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>To include google map on post or page you have to insert google map shortcode to the page content. You can do it by clicking on the following button in WYSIWYG editor:</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-508 --><article id="post-511" class="post-511 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">12.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-change-write-permissions" title="Permalink to How to change write permissions" rel="bookmark">How to change write permissions</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Our themes require write permissions on one folder and one file. Therefore you have to change write permissions on ait-cache directory which is in theme directory and on style.css (this file is dynamically generated using settings from AIT Admin).</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-511 --><article id="post-479" class="post-479 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">13.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-change-standard-design-layout-to-one-page-design-longpage-compound" title="Permalink to How can I change STANDARD design layout to ONE PAGE design (Longpage, Compound) ?" rel="bookmark">How can I change STANDARD design layout to ONE PAGE design (Longpage, Compound) ?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>On our preview sites you can sometimes see our products in different sizes like STANDARD, ONE PAGE or MINIMALISTIC design. There is no button for simple change from one to another. </p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-479 --><article id="post-1226" class="post-1226 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">14.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=work-global-local-settings" title="Permalink to Work with Global and Local settings" rel="bookmark">Work with Global and Local settings</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>In this template you can use two types of settings: Global settings Local settings Global settings Global settings can be found in the General Settings page. All what you have set up in these global settings is set up for all you pages. If you want to have slider, or for example the same appearance [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-1226 --><article id="post-481" class="post-481 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">15.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-turn-off-themebox-that-is-appearing-on-the-left-hand-side" title="Permalink to  How can I turn off themebox that is appearing on the left hand side?" rel="bookmark"> How can I turn off themebox that is appearing on the left hand side?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>You can turn it off in General settings -&gt; Show Themebox</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-481 --><article id="post-482" class="post-482 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">16.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-turn-off-ait-dashboard" title="Permalink to How can I turn off AIT Dashboard" rel="bookmark">How can I turn off AIT Dashboard</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>You can turn it on/off in config.php.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-482 --><article id="post-484" class="post-484 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">17.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-downloadupdate-my-theme" title="Permalink to  How can I download/update my theme?" rel="bookmark"> How can I download/update my theme?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>If you purchase our theme at ThemeForest site, all you need to do is just sign in with your username and password, and then download your chosen theme.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-484 --><article id="post-490" class="post-490 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">18.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-display-custom-widgets-on-individual-pages" title="Permalink to How to display custom widgets on individual pages" rel="bookmark">How to display custom widgets on individual pages</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>  We recommend you to installÂ Widget Logic pluginÂ in order to be able to control which widget can be shown on which page. After the plug-in is installed, a new âWidget Logicâ input box is displayed in the options box of every widget you use. In this box, you can type a series ofÂ WordPress conditional tagsÂ to [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-490 --><article id="post-2892" class="post-2892 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">19.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-configure-twitter-widget" title="Permalink to How to configure twitter widget" rel="bookmark">How to configure twitter widget</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Introduction AIT twitter widget displays chosen number of tweets from particular twitter user. Since twitter released its new API (1.1) there are few steps that need to be done before one can use AIT twitter widget. Because according to new twitter policy every API request needs to be authorized, one must first login to twitter [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-2892 --><article id="post-494" class="post-494 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">20.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-add-new-custom-cufon-font-to-wordpress-theme" title="Permalink to How to add new custom Cufon font to WordPress Theme" rel="bookmark">How to add new custom Cufon font to WordPress Theme</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>1. Please go to the following url to generate cufon: http://cufon.shoqolate.com/generate/ 2. Download your javascript font file and save it into design â &gt; fonts folder (in theme). This font will automatically appear in fonts dropdown in admin.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-494 --><article id="post-498" class="post-498 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">21.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-add-facebook-comments" title="Permalink to  How to add facebook comments" rel="bookmark"> How to add facebook comments</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Facebook comments can be added to every page. First we recommend you to disable default wordpress comments. Please click on the following tutorial if you are not sure how to disable wordpress comments.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-498 --><article id="post-503" class="post-503 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">22.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-add-facebook-box-like-plugin" title="Permalink to How to add facebook box (like plugin)" rel="bookmark">How to add facebook box (like plugin)</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>To show facebook box (like plugin) on post or page you have to insert facebook box shortcode to the page content. You can do it by clicking on the following button in WYSIWYG editor:</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-503 --><article id="post-504" class="post-504 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">23.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-speed-up-my-worpdress-site" title="Permalink to  How can I speed up my Worpdress site?" rel="bookmark"> How can I speed up my Worpdress site?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>If you are hosting your blog or cms website on shared hosting that is not really fast, we strongly recommend you using WP Super Cache plugin.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-504 --><article id="post-505" class="post-505 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">24.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-edit-po-translation-files" title="Permalink to How can I edit PO translation files?" rel="bookmark">How can I edit PO translation files?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Gettext PO file can be easily edited within wordpress admin using Codestyling Localization. You can also use standalone software like poEdit.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-505 --><article id="post-507" class="post-507 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">25.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-can-i-set-multiple-language-versions-of-my-website" title="Permalink to How can I set multiple language versions of my website?" rel="bookmark">How can I set multiple language versions of my website?</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>Our new themes are fully compatible with WPML wordpress plugin, we also included gettext PO file that can be used to translate system messages.</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-507 --><article id="post-3035" class="post-3035 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">26.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-create-child-theme" title="Permalink to How to create Child Theme" rel="bookmark">How to create Child Theme</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>In this article you can read how to create Child Theme from themes with our AIT Framework, starting from Creator theme to our newest themes. (find list of all our themes here) What are the most important parts in child theme? 1. ait-cache folder 2. Templates folder 3. style.css file Let’s explain whole process on [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-3035 --><article id="post-2548" class="post-2548 ait-doc type-ait-doc status-publish hentry no-thumbnail"><header class="entry-header"><div class="title-no-thumbnail">\n\n			<div class="no-thumb-img-description">\n				<div class="date">\n					<div class="day">27.</div><div class="month-year">STEP</div>\n					</div>\n			</div>\n\n			<h2 class="entry-title no-thumbnail"><a href="http://localhost/buscador/wp-admin/admin.php?page=ait-admin&amp;tab=faq&amp;qa=how-to-edit-custom-type" title="Permalink to How to edit Custom Type" rel="bookmark">How to edit Custom Type</a></h2>\n		</div>\n\n	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-summary dated-content">\n		<p>(example for WP Directory Item type) Following tutorial shows how to add few simple fields into your Item custom type in Directory theme (basically steps to edit other custom types in other themes are very similar…). Adding additional information for some custom type require: 1. Modify backend where you can store information for custom type. [...]</p>\n\n	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->\n\n  <!-- /.entry-meta -->\n</article><!-- /#post-2548 --></section></div>', 'no'),
(270, '_transient_timeout_doc_e0e5e3440509435f7c3c96620537de04', '1375457249', 'no'),
(271, '_transient_doc_e0e5e3440509435f7c3c96620537de04', '<div id="ait-theme-doc-single">\n			<h1>How to change write permissions</h1>\n            \n			<div class="ait-theme-doc-update">\n			 Updated: March 30, 2012, 12:08 pm\n			</div>\n            \n			<div class="theme-content-wrapper clear">\n							\n				<p> </p>\n<p>Our themes require write permissions on one folder and one file.</p>\n<p>Therefore you have to change write permissions onÂ <code>ait-cache</code>Â directory which is in theme directory and onÂ <code>style.css</code>Â (this file isÂ dynamically generated using settings from AIT Admin).</p>\n<h3><strong>If you have access to the server via SSH</strong></h3>\n<p>Use chmod command:</p>\n<p><code>chmod 0777 ait-cache style.css</code></p>\n<p>or with sudo</p>\n<p><code>sudo chmod 0777 ait-cache style.css</code></p>\n<h3><strong>If you have access to the server via FTP</strong></h3>\n<p>Use your favourite FTP client application to change permissions. For the following example we used Total Commander on Windows:<br/>\nFrom menuÂ <code>Files</code>Â choseÂ <code>Change Attributes...</code>Â And then enter 777 to text field or check all checkboxes.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ait-themes.com/wp-content/uploads/setattr.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-512" title="setattr" src="http://www.ait-themes.com/wp-content/uploads/setattr.png" alt="" width="402" height="453"/></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ait-themes.com/wp-content/uploads/777.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-513" title="777" src="http://www.ait-themes.com/wp-content/uploads/777.png" alt="" width="521" height="483"/></a></p>\n<p>This permission issue will be fixed in next releases of our AIT WordPress Framework. Weâre working hard on implementing WP Filesystem API for your convenience.</p>\n\n				\n			</div>\n		</div>', 'no'),
